Decorator that wraps a callback of VispyLabelsPolygonOverlay.

It ensures that the callback is only executed when all the conditions are met:
1) The overlay is enabled;
2) The number of displayed dimensions is 2 (it can only work in 2D);
3) The number of dimensions across which labels will be edited is 2.

If 2, 3 are not met, the Labels mode is automatically switched to PAN_ZOOM.

Send messages to clients.

These message go out once per frame. So it might not make sense to
include static information that rarely changes. Although if it's
small, maybe it's okay.

The message looks like:

{
    "poll": {
        "layers": {
            13482484: {
                "tile_state": ...
                "tile_config": ...
            }
        }
    }
}

Return mapping of field name -> dependent set of property names.

Dependencies will be guessed by inspecting the code of each property
in order to emit an event for a computed property when a model field
that it depends on changes (e.g: @property 'c' depends on model fields
'a' and 'b'). Alternatvely, dependencies may be declared excplicitly
in the Model Config.

Note: accessing a field with `getattr()` instead of dot notation won't
be automatically detected.

Examples
--------
    class MyModel(EventedModel):
        a: int = 1
        b: int = 1

        @property
        def c(self) -> List[int]:
            return [self.a, self.b]

        @c.setter
        def c(self, val: Sequence[int]):
            self.a, self.b = val

        @property
        def d(self) -> int:
            return sum(self.c)

        @d.setter
        def d(self, val: int):
            self.c = [val // 2, val // 2]

        class Config:
            dependencies={
                'c': ['a', 'b'],
                'd': ['a', 'b']
            }
